ğŸ”¹ 1ï¸âƒ£ LIST VM SIZES IN AZURE**
   ```bash
   # Get all available VM sizes in the 'westus' region
   az vm list-sizes --location westus --output table
âœ… This command retrieves a long list of VM sizes.

ğŸ”¹ 2ï¸âƒ£ FILTER OUTPUT USING GREP

# Find VM sizes that contain "DS"
az vm list-sizes --location westus --output table | grep DS
âœ… This filters the list to only show VM sizes containing "DS".

ğŸ”¹ 3ï¸âƒ£ APPLY A MORE SPECIFIC FILTER

# Find DS series VMs that are part of version 2
az vm list-sizes --location westus --output table | grep DS.*_v2
âœ… This narrows down results to DS VMs that belong to the V2 series.

